{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place flour, warm water, 2 tsp sugar, yeast and 1 tsp salt into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then knead <nobr>2 min\/<\/nobr>.","Transfer dough to a lightly floured surface and roll into a ball. Transfer to a large piece of parchment and roll out dough into a circle (approx. 14 in.) (see Tip). Slide the parchment onto a large baking sheet. Cover with a damp paper towel and let rest at room temperature. Meanwhile, make the sauce.","Preheat oven to 425°F. Lightly grease a pizza pan (14 in.) with olive oil and set aside.","Place mozzarella cheese into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place tomatoes, basil, oregano, 1 tsp sugar and ½ tsp salt into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and cook <nobr>25 min\/250°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Roll dough onto a lightly dusted rolling pin, then unroll dough onto prepared pizza pan. To create a border: fold over ½ inch of the dough edge and pinch to hold in place. Evenly sprinkle 5 oz of reserved grated cheese over the rested dough and cover with reserved tomato sauce. Sprinkle remaining 2 oz grated cheese over sauce. Brush edges of crust with 1 tbsp olive oil. Bake for 20-25 minutes (425°F) or until Tomato Pie is cooked through and browned to your liking.","Allow to cool slightly before slicing and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["7 oz all-purpose flour, plus extra to dust","4 oz warm water (approx. 100°F-110°F)","3 tsp sugar, divided","1 tsp rapid rise yeast","1 ½ tsp salt, divided","1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil, to brush, plus extra to grease","7 oz mozzarella cheese, cubed","22 oz fresh tomatoes, quartered","2 tsp dried basil","1 tsp dried oregano"]}],"id":"r361203","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-6nKXLRHmFqg\/XZVPHosmQ0I\/AAAAAAAAc1M\/IPQ-SoKi2sMOW7A7_u9Y